-- Ukraine’s Gross Foreign Debt Climbs 0.9% as Borrowing Increases
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2013-06-19T15:04:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-19/ukraine-s-gross-foreign-debt-climbs-0-9-as-borrowing-increases.html
Ukraine’s gross foreign debt grew
0.9 percent in the first quarter from the previous three months
as government, banks and companies tapped international markets.  Debt rose to $136.3 billion as of April 1, equal to 76.9
percent of gross domestic product, from $135.1 billion on Jan.
1, the  Natsionalnyi Bank Ukrainy , based in the capital, Kiev,
said today on its website.  More than 76 percent of the total was denominated in
dollars, the central bank said.  Short-term debt that matures in the next 12 months fell 0.2
percent to $60.1 billion in the first quarter, according to the
central bank.  -- Editors: Paul Abelsky, Leon Mangasarian  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
